Results

Alaa Aldoh

Last compiled on 15 March, 2023

1 Methods

1.1 Participants

A total of 1530 started the study, and 1489 completed the study. After excluding participants who started the study more than once (n = 10, total of 22 cases), a total of 1508 cases remained. Of the 1508 unique participants that took part in the study, 1250 completed the second survey (82.89% completion rate). 30 were excluded for indicating that they were vegan or vegetarian, 57 were excluded for spending less than 5 seconds on the reading task, and 108 were excluded because they were multivariate outliers. The final sample consisted of 1294 participants.

1.2 Missing data

Around 15-16% of values were missing across outcomes measured at T2.
